-- Hungary Stocks: OTP Bank, Est Media Move in Budapest Trading
-- B y   A n d r a s   G e r g e l y
-- 2012-07-18T15:21:58Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-18/hungary-stocks-otp-bank-est-media-move-in-budapest-trading.html
The benchmark  BUX (BUX)  index climbed for
a fourth day, adding 0.3 percent to 17,332.33 by the close in
Budapest.  The following were among the most active shares in the
Hungarian market today. Stock symbols follow company names.  OTP Bank Nyrt. (OTP)   Hungary’s largest lender, rose 0.5
percent to 3,470 forint. European stocks advanced for the third
time in four days after lenders including Credit Suisse Group AG
reported profits that beat estimates, while minutes showed the
 Bank of England  may reconsider the case for an interest-rate
cut.  Est Media Vagyonkezelo Nyrt. (ESTMEDIA HB), a Hungarian
entertainment company, fell the most in three months after
agreeing to sell a stake in the country’s biggest outdoor
festival to its minority owners. The shares dropped 15 percent
to 23 forint.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andras Gergely in Budapest at 
